Results.ReviewText: amazing just amazing  classic taste and worth the price
Results.Title: aroma

Results.ReviewText: We only drink Barista Style Gold Blend because it's the BEST tasting of all the Gold Blend Nescafé coffees .You get what you pay for! It's bursting with flavour.Intense&robust .As its instant it's less time consuming to make than ground coffee.Barista Style Gold Blend is a convenient ,tasty ,easy way to enjoy coffee that tastes every bit as good as coffee served in a coffee shop by a barista !We love it!We drink it morning until evening.The smile in a mug!
Results.Title: The best flavour of all the Nescafé coffees!

Results.ReviewText: I usually use a "pod" coffee machine or cafetiere with freshly ground beans to get the taste I want. Occasionally I do not have much time and have a cup of instant coffee which, till now, has not tasted the same. I purchased a tub of Gold Blend Barista style and was very surprised by how good and authentic it tasted. Compared with coffee pods, this is excellent value for money, and does not compromise on coffee taste. An excellent instant coffee
Results.Title: Great Coffee

Results.ReviewText:
I have always drunk Nescafe Gold Blend coffee for as long as I can remember, that was until I recently decided to try Nescafe Gold Blend Barista.  I cannot fault any Nescafe coffee but this one really does exceed the rest.  The taste is rich and strong, absolutely superb and I would even go as far as to say that its as good or if not better than most coffees bought in coffee shops.  You will not be disappointed if 
you buy this.
Results.Title: Brilliant Barista

Results.ReviewText: This is now the only coffee I will drink, so much so that if I go out I tend to drink tea as I can't stand the taste (other than the odd cappucino).  I love the way the coffee hits the back of your throat and is full of flavour but at the same time the taste is not overpoweringly strong.  I drink about 6 cups a day (with semi skimmed milk) and am destraught if I run out so always have a couple of tins in the cupboard as back up.
Results.Title: The only coffee for me

Results.ReviewText:
I happened across this in our local supermarket & as I used to work as a barista around 10 years ago, the name appealed to me so I decided to give it a try :)
The tin seems good quality & the smell on opening was gorgeous & rich x
It did seem initially quite expensive, but the taste more than justifies the price tag! I'd recommend investing in a milk frother & bingo, High End coffee straight from your kitchen!!!
Results.Title: Better than High Street Coffee Shops!!!

Results.ReviewText: Very impressed with the Nescafé Gold Blend Barista Style - my husband tells me it has a smooth taste, makes a 'cracking' cup of coffee and is saving us a fortune on coffee shop bought brands.  Serving suggestion (for hubby at least) is make in a 'takeout' cup, head to the car, spill as you put it in the cup holder then enjoy the taste and sensation of waking up with a hot and tasty coffee as you drive to work.
Results.Title: Costa lot less for the family!

Results.ReviewText:
First tried this when I saw it on promotion whilst doing our weekly "Big Shop" and dropped a tin in to the trolley to try. 
I am so pleased I did. Big strong coffee flavour for a great start to my day and now have a tin at work to share with Colleagues and visitors.
Most people comment on how nice it is to go so where and have a great cup of coffee with out the Barrista price tag.
Results.Title: Proper Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I bought this when shopping at Sainsbury's. I do like this style of coffee but often find it can be bitter but not this product. Let the water cool slightly from the boil and create in a pre-warmed cup. This is such a blissful coffee; the aroma is magnificent, the taste is sublime, it is everything you want from a coffee and without all of the fuss of filter or other methods.
Results.Title: How Coffee should taste

Results.ReviewText: Nescafé Gold has always been that standard by which all other coffees are compared, for example, that's nice but not a patch on Nescafé Gold. Now there is Nescafé Gold Barista style which pushes the bar to an even higher level. From that first "Pssst" as you break the deal with the wonderful aroma that greets you to the dregs of your last cup there is nothing better.
Results.Title: The Gold Standard

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying Barista style for over 3 months now in addition to my regular Nescafe. The flavour and texture are so exquisite that I see this as a treat when I want to indulge myself. It is also my first port of call when I have special visitors. It definitely gives the impression that you are drinking a very expensive filter coffee. No more cafetieres for me!
Results.Title: Smooth Flavour

Results.ReviewText: For the last couple of years I've been using a coffee pod machine.The pods have slowly crept up in price so decided on a change.Chose the Barista blend as I didn't want some "slop dishwater stuff".This coffee doesn't disappoint strong and flavoursome I dont have sugar with mine which is fine as its not at all bitter.Coffee machine has gone to the charity shop.
Results.Title: decent coffee

Results.ReviewText:
Who knew satisfying coffee could be so FAST!
Let's face it, you either love the ritual of making real coffee or hate it. When I'm desperate for a coffee with a kick I don't want to wait. Nescafé Gold Blend Barista Style fits the bill admirably. A super rich taste, gorgeous aroma, it's my go -to coffee these days. Well done Nescafé,; the pleasure's all mine !!
Results.Title: Who knew?

Results.ReviewText:
Totally amazed after trying this product. I do not visit major coffee shop chains as the coffee never tastes nice and rarely tastes the same. 

Saw the ‘Barista style’ in my supermarket and decided to give it a try. So glad I did as the taste is superb. I will never be setting foot in a coffee shop again as long as I have a tin on Nescafé in my cupboard.
Results.Title: Better than major coffee shops!

Results.ReviewText: I am on my second tub of this coffee I have one cup first thing on a morning before work then I take it to work with me. I have one before I start work then on every break I even have other people hooked on it the taste is so good and refreshing I even stopped drinking my chocolate mocha. This is the taste of the future so don’t stop making it please
Results.Title: Amazing taste that sets you up for the day

Results.ReviewText: I bought the Barista gold blend last weekend, not my normal coffee but my cafetiere broke and I was looking for a quick fix!  Loved the smell on opening the tin which was rich and strong.  On tasting it, I felt as close to my brewed coffee as I have had for a while, will definitely try it again.  Love the tin also - eyes on it for a pencil holder!
Results.Title: Fab deep taste, lovely aroman

Results.ReviewText: Tried this for the first time recently  -  WOW !   I am and always have been an original Nescafe girl.  Dont get me wrong - I've tried others but always come back to Nescafe original.   But this new Barista - "B" for Beesknees !   It taste so much richer - deeper.  Its now got pride of place in my kitchen  -  its my Hug in a Mug !  Love it !!!!
Results.Title: Converted original Nescafe girl

Results.ReviewText: I decided to try this coffee recently and I'm SO glad I did. I like strong, full bodied coffee and this definitely fits the criteria! I used to spend so much on going to coffee shops but now it's brilliant that I can have the same quality at home (and save some money in the process!) Coffee lovers try this - you won't regret it. Bravo Nescafe!
Results.Title: Coffee shop quality at home

Results.ReviewText: We use this coffee at work, everyone loves it and a few have converted to using it at home as well. Before you can even think about starting work you need a good coffee to alert your senses and this one hits the Mark. I remember collecting labels for free mugs, have you thought of doing this again, I'm down to my last two lol.
Results.Title: Great tasting coffee

Results.ReviewText: I was lucky enough to first purchase this on a half price offer but am now converted! It honestly does taste like a coffee from a coffee shop- it is full bodied without being overly strong and I find the tin very useful at keeping the coffee fresh and also to use afterwards as a container! I have mine black and it is perfect.
Results.Title: Fabulous!

Results.ReviewText: We have always loved our Nescafé coffee and Barista Gold truly lives up to our expectations. Full of flavour with a real fresh ground taste that you normally only get when visit an authentic coffee house. However Barista Gold brings all the benefits of a good fresh ground coffee to our home whenever we want it. Great!
Results.Title: Barista Gold

Results.ReviewText: I brought this  as a replacement as I cold nt buy my normal coffee and I was NOT disappointed! The taste the smell... the aroma...the smoothness  Just as you'd expect from a  high end coffee shop  but such great value.. .... just awesome.. This is now TOP of my list ..a MUST buy for anyone who loves coffee
Results.Title: Superb Packaging Superb Taste

Results.ReviewText: I thought this may be a little bitter and strong and it wasn't It had a beautiful aroma  The type that makes you pause and sniff over and over again.Lift up the cup and taste. A product that you can rely on time  after time .Fine grains mix easily and never change.Perfect product in a can .Wonderful.
Results.Title: Absolutely wonderful taste and blended just right

Results.ReviewText: i was offered a cup of Gold Barista at my daughters house when i was on a visit and found it to have a wonderful mellow taste that combine the rich taste of original coffee with a wonderful new experience of soft relaxing and comforting taste. next time i am in the shop this will be a definite buy
Results.Title: excellent prominent lettering

Results.ReviewText: I have a bean coffee machine at home and love barista coffee, but sometimes I just don't have the time to set my machine up or clean it afterwards. Gold Blend barista style coffee is the closest that I have found to freshly ground bean coffee. I would recommend this coffee to my friends & family.
Results.Title: Close to the real thing!

Results.ReviewText: I normally drink gold blend original as my "go to" morning coffee. I tried Barista Style out of curiosity and was impressed. Nice velvety texture which classic gold blend flavour. Ever so slightly more bitter after taste than original which I personally like. Over all a good every day coffee.
Results.Title: Rich and Welcoming!

Results.ReviewText: Been a Nescafé original drinker for more years than I can remember, then 3 weeks ago I bought Nescafe Gold Blend Barista Style 'to have a change'.  What a change!  It's so full bodied with a real deep flavour and taste. For coffee connoisseurs it's the one! I'm certainly not changing back.
Results.Title: It's the one

Results.ReviewText: I purchased this when it was on special offer at my local supermarket. I love a decent cup of coffee and find it hard to replicate the coffee shop taste and intensity at home. This coffee did exactly that. Smooth, dark, full of rich flavours and delicious. It felt like an indulgent treat.
Results.Title: Just like a cup from a coffee shop

Results.ReviewText: I was bought this coffe by my Son who likes it a lot.  It was a very good 'upgrade' from my ususal Gold Blend coffee which I usually have. It actually reminds me of my holidays in Tuscany, italy, Coffee in the mornings.  I will more than likely try it again twhen this tin is finished.
Results.Title: Very smooth

Results.ReviewText: I like a good strong tasting coffee usually black but most have a bitter aftertaste, so it was most refreshing to find that this blend has a strong taste without any unpleasant aftertaste, no better  way to start the day....mmmm maybe someone should use that in an add campaign !!
Results.Title: good starter

Results.Description: A well-rounded, smooth coffee with a rich aroma.
